================================================================================
OPTIMAL b(n) Calculation - Standard Normal (500 ITERATIONS)
================================================================================
CONFIGURATION:
  - Distribution: N(0,1) - NO TRUNCATION
  - k = 2e8 samples per n value
  - n range: [2, 100]
  - 500 iterations with different seeds
  - Solve: 1 = mean(sqrt(sum_sq_dev / (n-b(n))))
  - Find optimal b(n) that makes estimator unbiased
  - Memory strategy: Process n-values in batches
================================================================================
JAX version: 0.8.0
JAX backend: gpu
Start time: 2025-11-08 21:35:16
Logging to: optimal_bn_log.txt

GPU: NVIDIA GeForce RTX 4090
Memory at startup:
  Used:    415 MB (  1.7%)
  Free:  23667 MB ( 96.3%)
  Total: 24564 MB
================================================================================


Batch Parameters:
  k = 200,000,000 samples per n value
  n range: [2, 100] (99 points)
  Number of iterations: 500
  Distribution: Standard Normal N(0,1) - NO TRUNCATION
  Goal: Find b(n) such that mean(sqrt(sum_sq_dev/(n-b(n)))) = 1

  MEMORY STRATEGY:
  - Process n-values in 4 batches of 32 values each
  - RAM per batch: ~47.7 GB (fits in 64 GB)
  - Total n-values: 99

Determining safe chunk size:
  Free memory: 23667 MB
  Usable (60%): 14200 MB
  Max safe chunk: 7,755,202
  Selected: 500,000

  Estimated need:     1416 MB

  Safety limit:      22108 MB (90% of total)

  Status: SAFE - 20277 MB margin
